commit.message:
New version: 0.22

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Add changelog entry for version 0.22

Dispense with the precise date. It causes a serious amount of additional
work to try to maintain it.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Be less specific about the error returned by remove_filter

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Use 4.11.7 version of hypothesis

Released shortly after the default version of pytest for xenial.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Do not check device properties against the udevadm oracle

It is not reliable enough:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1787089

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Manually add a six.moves entry for collections

Direct imports of the abstract classes from collections will go away
entirely in Python 3.9.

Manually add instead of using six's newly introduced offical move because
a lot of distros are going to be slow to update to a new version of six
because they are phasing out Python 2 anyway.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Remove byte modifier from autodoc-process-docstring

It was probably added accidentally and worked on Python 2 but will not
work on Python 3.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Disable a pylint error

It must be intentional not to also invoke Container's __init__ method.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Remove support for privileged tests

Over the years, only the one that was allowed on Travis was executed,
and there is not enough knowledge of pytest to revive them.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Moving pylint version back to 1.9.4

It is loaded for every Travis task, and is not available for Python 3.7.
The right thing to do is to require the things that are needed task by task
but this will do for now.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Disable an import error for wx

To keep pylint happy.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Invoke superclass initializer to avoid a pylint error

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Run pylint under Python 2.7

The version of pylint we are using seems to crash on Python 3.7.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Do not test on Python 3.4

Do test on Python 3.7.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Move pylint up to most recent Python 2 compatible version

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Remove a test that requires attribute values to be stable

They don't really stay stable long enough.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Remove test_device_file

It relies on correctness of DEVLINKS. See commit
359c64509cddce55d3432995d4e5c28dccc9d7c5 for an explanation of why this is
not a mistake.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Remove test_from_device_file_links

It is intended to test pyudev, but what it always ends up doing is
finding new subsystems that are messing up their DEVLINKS field.
It's not our business to report the mistakes that these subsystems are
making. Even when we do report, the problem never is fixed:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1263441.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

Don't use min_satisfying_examples in tests

This parameter was removed by Hypothesis in v4.0.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>

tests: use pytest.ini instead of setup.cfg to configure pytest

Signed-off-by: Filipe Laíns <lains@archlinux.org>

Use getfixturevalue instead of getfuncargvalue

getfuncarvalue was removed in pytest 4.0, now available.
Move pytest requirement up to 3.0, when getfixturevalue was first introduced.

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>
tests: fix tests for pytest 4.0

Disable a new and erroneous pylint error

Signed-off-by: mulhern <amulhern@redhat.com>
Update hypothesis from 3.64.0 to 3.66.1
